Articles.Content:
Thanks for the feedback everyone!

@Gaiiden - Good idea! I could create some sort of "pop off" button that would spawn another window for the selected part. That will take a bit of work though. At the same time I'd like to start linking the window states to the active vessel - right now when you switch vessels then go back it forgets what part you had selected before. The final piece would be to save the various window states so they persist across different gaming sessions.

@Svm420 - Also a good idea! I managed to find where those temperature fields are stored on the part, so adding them will be easy enough. Perhaps as a default I will display something like "current temp / max temp" and only display the others when the debug option is enabled.
